stylometry: The trade off between price and demand is relatively simple. If you produce too much at a low price, you might sell alot, but profits may be low because the more you produce the more your cost will go up as well. If you produce a small amount of goods you have to sell them at a higher price which means people may not buy them, but because you are not producing as many cost goes down. A model to solve this probem must look at demand, price, and cost. It must figure out the most effective way to maximize profit by taking these considerations all into account. The number produced would be a changing cell and you would have constraints as any constraints you might have on labor hours, workers, materials, etc. and you would be trying to maximize profit.
